The paper proposes a new variant of neural networks for analyzing tensorial time series data, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed method is based on tensor Tucker decomposition, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision and image processing (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the limitations of traditional recurrent neural networks and proposes a solution for learning the representation of longitudinal data, which is a topic related to neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE). Finally, the proposed method can be applied to various fields such as healthcare, finance, and social sciences, which are topics related to social and information sciences (cs.SI).
